The paper discusses the challenges and opportunities of analyzing visual lifelogging data, which involves processing and understanding images captured by a camera worn by the user. This topic is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
